label: Versus Fn type of object type of stuff
(VersusFn ObjectType StuffType)
items.comment: Note that specializations of instances of ObjectType need not themselves be instances of ObjectType, and some specializations of instances of StuffType need not themselves be instances of StuffType. For example, Event is an instance of TemporalStuffType, but some specializations of Event, such as LunarRoundTrip, are instances of TemporalObjectType. Events qua Events are temporally stuff-like, but Events qua $LunarRoundTrips are temporally object-like. To put it another way, if one cuts an Event in half into two time slices, one is left with two things which are themselves Events. On the other hand, if one cuts a LunarRoundTrip in half, one is left with two objects that are *not* LunarRoundTrips. Those two time slice objects are, however, Events.

An unreifiable BinaryFunction that takes a PartiallyTangible and a TemporalThing and returns a NetWorkQuantity. ((QPQuantityFn NetWorkQuantity) OBJ TEMP-THING) denotes the net quantity of work done on OBJ in TEMP-THING, i.e., the sum of the quantities of work done by each force acting on OBJ in TEMP-THING.

In classical mechanics, work is by definition the magnitude of force times the magnitude of displacement times the cosine of the angle between the force and the displacement. In the special case where the force and the displacement are in the same direction, work is simply magnitude of force times magnitude of displacement.
